Comment: Anhydrite dominates with radiolarians, diatoms, and very rare foraminifers.
Foraminifers dominate with diatoms and radiolarians.
Dominated by planktonic foraminifers with few deep water benthonic foraminifers and a few shallow types;  with tubes of pyrite crystals, some green tubes.
Pyrite dominates with agglutinated foraminifers, calcite benthonic foraminifers, and few planktonic foraminifers which have overgrowths. Anhydrite or gypsum crystals.
